console.views.application-integrations-l:
With the LoRa Cloud Device & Application Services protocol, you can manage common device functionality at the application layer for LoRaWANÂ®-enabled devices. This protocol consists of a set of messages that are exchanged on a predefined device management LoRaWAN port (199 by default). The purpose of these messages is three-fold:
  1. Periodically communicate info messages
  2. Trigger client-initiated management commands
  3. Run advanced, application-layer protocols which solve common LoRaWAN use cases
